PREFLIGHT CHECKLIST — PeanutTrade Arb Bot
==========================================
Run through before each live session.

ACCOUNTS
[ ] Binance API key active (Profile -> API Management)
[ ] Binance LINK balance >= 1.5 (enough for 1+ trade)
[ ] Binance USDT balance visible
[ ] Wallet address confirmed in .env (ADDR=)
[ ] Wallet ETH balance >= 0.0005 (gas on Arbitrum One)
[ ] Wallet USDT balance >= 15.00 (enough for 1 DEX buy)

CONFIGURATION
[ ] ARB_RPC_URL set and reachable
[ ] PRIVATE_KEY set (new MetaMask wallet, not old compromised key)
[ ] BINANCE_API_KEY and BINANCE_SECRET set (new keys post-Day 4)
[ ] BINANCE_USDT_DEPOSIT_ADDRESS set

KILL SWITCH
[ ] No file at C:\arb_bot_kill (would pause trading immediately)
[ ] Circuit breaker reset (not in cooldown from previous session)

CONNECTIVITY TEST
[ ] python scripts/check_pnl.py   -- shows live balances from both venues
[ ] python scripts/arb_bot.py --mode prod --dry-run  -- signals generate, no trades

RISK LIMITS (verify match intended day)
[ ] --day 4: max_trade_usd=$15, max_daily_loss=$20, max_drawdown=20%
[ ] Consecutive loss limit: 3 (pauses after 3 losses in a row)

MONITORING
[ ] Telegram bot token set (optional but useful for alerts)
[ ] Prometheus port 8000 free (or metrics_port=0 to disable)

KNOWN ISSUES / REMINDERS
- LINK deposits to Binance: use BEP20 (BSC) network, NOT Arbitrum One
- USDT deposits to Binance: Arbitrum One network works
- If inventory_ok=False: buy LINK on Binance, wait 30s for auto-sync
- If circuit breaker trips: wait 10 min or restart bot
- Emergency liquidation: python emergency_liquidate.py --execute
